# Data Preparation Summary - E-Commerce Churn Analysis

### 1. Assess Dataset & Cleaning
* Missing Values: NA
* Duplicates: NA
* Date Formatting: Converted 'signup_date', 'last_purchase_date', and 'order_date' to standard datetime format.

### 2. Feature Engineering (New Variables Created)
* Order_amount: Calculated as unit_price x quantity
* Recency (recency_days): Calculated as days since the last purchase to quantify customer engagement.
* Tenure (tenure_days): Total duration from signup to the current analysis date.
* Monetary (monetary): Derived total spending per customer (Unit Price x Quantity).
* Avg_Order_Value: Average spending per transaction.
* Purchase_Intensity: Ratio of purchase frequency to tenure to identify high-activity users.
* Inactivity_Ratio: Proportion of customer life-cycle spent without purchasing.

### 3. Outlier 
* Numerical Outliers: Identified in 'unit_price', 'avg_order_value', and 'purchase_intensity'.
* Strategic Retention: These outliers have been RETAINED in the cleaned file to ensure the model captures the 40% revenue risk tied to high-value/at-risk segments. 
* Modeling: Tree-based models are able to handle these variances.

